==Old English==

===Etymology===
Common Germanic, from an Indo-European base ''*kuos, *kuod''.

Germanic cognates include Old Frisian [[hwet]], Old Saxon [[hwat]] (Dutch [[wat]]), Old High German [[hwaz]] (German [[was]]), Old Norse [[hvat]] (Swedish [[vad]]), Gothic [[𐍈𐌰]].

The Indo-European root also led to Latin [[quod]] and Lithuanian [[kàd]].

